citeinfo.origin: Great Barrier Reef Marine Park Authority
citeinfo.title: SDC.GBR_FEATURES

descript.abstract: - Coastal features within and adjacent to the Great Barrier Reef World Heritage area (such as islands, rocks and the Queensland mainland). - Major coral cay features - Major and other coral reef structures (as defined by the reef shoal edge) and tidal, drying or emergent reef areas within the Great Barrier Reef World Heritage Area
descript.purpose: To represent Great Barrier Reef Marine Park features within and adjacent to the GBRWHA

theme.themekt: REQUIRED: Reference to a formally registered thesaurus or a similar authoritative source of theme keywords.

idinfo.accconst: The Data is subject to Copyright. Usage must comply with signed data usage agreement. Appropriate acknowledgement of the custodian must be created in all outputs. No third party usage is permitted without prior written consent of the custodian.
idinfo.useconst: REQUIRED: Restrictions and legal prerequisites for using the data set after access is granted.

cntorgp.cntorg: Great Barrier Reef Marine Park Authority

idinfo.native: Microsoft Windows XP Version 5.1 (Build 2600) Service Pack 2; ESRI ArcCatalog 9.3.1.1850

attracc.attraccr: Accuracy for attributes estimated to be better than 95% correct.

dataqual.logic: Drying reef areas are logically consistent (i.e.: are completely contained within) indicative reef boundaries
dataqual.complete: Major reef areas, and major exposed portions are present. Smaller exposed areas and shoals may not be present.

horizpa.horizpar: The features have not been statistically tested with precision survey techniques. Positional accuracy varies considerably and dataset should NOT be used for navigation purposes, however, for general use the coverage can be regarded as having a nominal scale of 1:250,000.

altsys.altenc: Explicit elevation coordinate included with horizontal coordinates

attr.attrdef: A number that is made up of a two-digit number representing the latitude band the feature is in and a three -digit number representing features belonging to each other e.g. an island with an adjacent reef/cay/rock etc should have the same SORT_GBR_I (eg Goldsmith Island 20-237 plus Goldsmith Island Reef (No 1) 20-237a etc))
GBR_ID plus SUB_NO plus FEATURE_C with hyphens (eg 19-063-101-104)
GBR_ID plus SUB_NO plus FEATURE_C with with no hyphens. This is to be used as the unique ID for the oracle database (eg 19063101104)

attrdomv.udom: Sequential unique whole numbers that are automatically generated.

attr.attrdef: A three-digit number that identifies multiple features of the same type in a group, e.g. multiple reefs surrounding an island are labelled a, b, c, d etc - these will be numbered 101, 102, 103, 104 etc. If it refers to a single feature it will be given the number 100
Type of feature: Cay, Island, Mainland, Reef, Rock or Sand
Queensland Government Previous name for feature
Original label with "S" identifier for single features
Previous version label from RAP process
Short name of feature with identifying ID for Oracle database (50 characters)

attrdomv.udom: Positive real numbers that are automatically generated.

attr.attrdef: Long name of feature with identifying ID for Oracle database (255 characters)

attrdomv.udom: Positive real numbers that are automatically generated.

attr.attrdef: A three-digit number representing the type of feature eg mainland, island, cay etc (100, 102, 103)

attrdomv.udom: Positive real numbers that are automatically generated.

attr.attrdef: Latitude: centroid of feature given in decimal degrees

attrdomv.udom: Positive real numbers that are automatically generated.

attr.attrdef: Longitude: centroid of feature given in decimal degrees

dataIdInfo.idAbs: Coastal features within and adjacent to the Great Barrier Reef World Heritage area (such as the Queensland Mainland and Islands, Indicative Reef boundaries and Rocks.). Major coral cay features,major and other coral reef structures (as defined by the reef shoal edge) and tidal, drying or emergent reef areas within the Great Barrier Reef World Heritage Area.
dataIdInfo.idPurp: To represent Great Barrier Reef Marine Park features within and adjacent to the Great Barrier Reef World Heritage Area. This includes the Great Barrier Reef Mainland and Islands, Indicative Reef boundaries and Rocks.

idPoC.rpOrgName: Great Barrier Reef Marine Park Authority

dataIdInfo.idCredit: The Data is subject to Copyright. Products should show acknowledgement in the form of "Data courtesy of the Great Barrier Reef Marine Park Authority".

Consts.useLimit: Usage must comply with signed data usage agreement. Appropriate acknowledgement of the custodian must be created in all outputs. No third party usage is permitted without prior written consent of the custodian.

dataIdInfo.suppInfo: The coastline of Queensland was produced under specific contract for GBRMPA by AUSLIG in 1984. Originally engineered by AUSLIG from datasets produced by the Division of National Mapping and RAN Hydrographic Service; Queensland coastal information produced by AUSLIG at 250k scale with 100k elements from developing technology at the time of genesis; Island information is specific to the Great Barrier Reef Region as produced from RAN Hydrographic Service data at 100k scale; mangrove information at 250k scale as produced by AUSLIG.

report.measDesc: Drying reef areas are logically consistent (i.e.: are completely contained within) indicative reef boundaries.
Major reef areas, and major exposed portions are present. Smaller exposed areas and shoals may not be present.
Accuracy for attributes estimated to be better than 95% correct.

The features have not been statistically tested with precision survey techniques. Positional accuracy varies considerably and dataset should NOT be used for navigation purposes, however, for general use the coverage can be regarded as having a nominal scale of 1:250,000.

dataLineage.statement:
July 2002 Updated in July 2002 to improve the logical consistency with other GBRMPA datasets (ZONING, REEFS, ROCKS). Represents a combined dataset inlcuding elements from CAYS and ROCKS. Features with diameter < 100m extracted to form a symbolised ROCKS coverage.
2003-2004 Updated against satellite imagery during the RAP process (2003-2004) to 25k scale, especially in Cairns, Whitsundays and Hinchinbrook Regions.
Callum Shoal defined from Navigational Chart, Reef ID added 20-1271.
2008 Update to dry reef around Low Island and Woody Island as part of Cairns Plan of Management Review (Jan 2008).
2008 Update to indicative reef at Bait Reef as part of Cairns Plan of Management Review (Jan 2008).
21 October 2013 Reef 21-284 named Ron Taylor Reef
22 October 2013 Barren Island Reef (No.3) (23-031c) added (area drawn from Keppels No Anchoring Area)
19 January 2015 U/N Reef 17-065 named Bob Endean Reef (17-065)
17 March 2016 U/N Reef 20-389 named Neville Coleman Reef
28 October 2016 U/N Reef 17-069 named Peter Arnold Reef
06 March 2017 U/N Reef 14-140 named Sydney Schubert Reef
06 March 2017 U/N Reef 18-022 named Felicity Wishart Reef
20 October 2017 U/N Reef 22-101 named Don Kinsey Reef
24 November 2017 U/N Island 17-013b named Catalina Rock
20 November 2018 Yuindalla Island 20-075c name corrected to Yiundalla Island 20-075c Blackcurrent Island 20-010b name corrected to Black Current Island 20-010b
As directed by the state of Queensland: Nigger Head Reef 11-146 repealed and reinstated to U/N Reef status Nigger Head 11-146 repealed and reinstated to U/N Cay status
